The family spokesperson, Sipho Makhabane, confirmed to TshisaLIVE that the funeral service will take place at 9am at the Moses Mabhida Stadium in Durban this Saturday, 10 December.There will be two memorial services for the late gospel icon, one in Durban and one in Johannesburg.The one in Durban will take place at the Ethekwini Community Church (ECC) on Thursday, 8 December at 11am.The family has not yet confirmed the venue for the Johannesburg memorial service, however, it's set to be held on Friday, 9 December.More details to follow.Sfiso died on Monday morning after being rushed to a Johannesburg hospital. Sipho confirmed to TshisaLIVE that he had suffered from kidney failure. video 